  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, tear your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> into the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally until golden and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669742947080-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669742947080-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669742947080-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669742947080-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669742947080-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, add your <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>tortiglioni for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> cooked tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a large cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669742951263-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669742951263-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669742951263-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669742951263-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669742951263-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Once the mushrooms are golden, reduce the heat to medium-high and add your <strong>lean pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!)</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669742954383-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
